#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an7.51"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an7.51:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 7 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 7 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an7.51:0.2"
msgid "5. Mahāyaññavagga "
msgstr "5. A Great Sacrifice "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 51. Saṃyogasutta → saṃyogavisaṃyogadhammapariyāyasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an7.51:0.3"
msgid "51. Saṃyogasutta "
msgstr "51. Bound and Unbound "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.57, sc1
msgctxt "an7.51:1.1"
msgid "“Saṃyogavisaṃyogaṃ vo, bhikkhave, dhammapariyāyaṃ desessāmi. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, I will teach you an exposition of the teaching on the bound and the unbound. "

msgctxt "an7.51:1.2"
msgid "Taṃ suṇātha … pe … "
msgstr "Listen and pay close attention, I will speak. … "

msgctxt "an7.51:1.3"
msgid "katamo ca so, bhikkhave, saṃyogo visaṃyogo dhammapariyāyo? "
msgstr "And what is the exposition of the teaching on the bound and the unbound? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an7.51:2.1"
msgid "Itthī, bhikkhave, ajjhattaṃ itthindriyaṃ manasi karoti—"
msgstr "A woman focuses on her own femininity: "

msgctxt "an7.51:2.2"
msgid "itthikuttaṃ itthākappaṃ itthividhaṃ itthicchandaṃ itthissaraṃ itthālaṅkāraṃ. "
msgstr "her feminine moves, feminine appearance, feminine ways, feminine desires, feminine voice, and feminine adornment. "

msgctxt "an7.51:2.3"
msgid "Sā tattha rajjati tatrābhiramati. "
msgstr "She’s stimulated by this and takes pleasure in it. "

msgctxt "an7.51:2.4"
msgid "Sā tattha rattā tatrābhiratā bahiddhā purisindriyaṃ manasi karoti—"
msgstr "So she focuses on the masculinity of others: "

msgctxt "an7.51:2.5"
msgid "purisakuttaṃ purisākappaṃ purisavidhaṃ purisacchandaṃ purisassaraṃ purisālaṅkāraṃ. "
msgstr "masculine moves, masculine appearance, masculine ways, masculine desires, masculine voice, and masculine adornment. "

msgctxt "an7.51:2.6"
msgid "Sā tattha rajjati tatrābhiramati. "
msgstr "She’s stimulated by this and takes pleasure in it. "

msgctxt "an7.51:2.7"
msgid "Sā tattha rattā tatrābhiratā bahiddhā saṃyogaṃ ākaṅkhati. "
msgstr "So she desires to bond with another. "

msgctxt "an7.51:2.8"
msgid "Yañcassā saṃyogapaccayā uppajjati sukhaṃ somanassaṃ tañca ākaṅkhati. "
msgstr "And she desires the pleasure and happiness that comes from such a bond. "

msgctxt "an7.51:2.9"
msgid "Itthatte, bhikkhave, abhiratā sattā purisesu saṃyogaṃ gatā. "
msgstr "Sentient beings who are attached to their femininity are bound to men. "

msgctxt "an7.51:2.10"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, itthī itthattaṃ nātivattati. "
msgstr "This is how a woman does not transcend her femininity. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.58, sc3
msgctxt "an7.51:3.1"
msgid "Puriso, bhikkhave, ajjhattaṃ purisindriyaṃ manasi karoti—"
msgstr "A man focuses on his own masculinity: "

msgctxt "an7.51:3.2"
msgid "purisakuttaṃ purisākappaṃ purisavidhaṃ purisacchandaṃ purisassaraṃ purisālaṅkāraṃ. "
msgstr "his masculine moves, masculine appearance, masculine ways, masculine desires, masculine voice, and masculine adornment. "

msgctxt "an7.51:3.3"
msgid "So tattha rajjati tatrābhiramati. "
msgstr "He’s stimulated by this and takes pleasure in it. "

msgctxt "an7.51:3.4"
msgid "So tattha ratto tatrābhirato bahiddhā itthindriyaṃ manasi karoti—"
msgstr "So he focuses on the femininity of others: "

msgctxt "an7.51:3.5"
msgid "itthikuttaṃ itthākappaṃ itthividhaṃ itthicchandaṃ itthissaraṃ itthālaṅkāraṃ. "
msgstr "feminine moves, feminine appearance, feminine ways, feminine desires, feminine voice, and feminine adornment. "

msgctxt "an7.51:3.6"
msgid "So tattha rajjati tatrābhiramati. "
msgstr "He’s stimulated by this and takes pleasure in it. "

msgctxt "an7.51:3.7"
msgid "So tattha ratto tatrābhirato bahiddhā saṃyogaṃ ākaṅkhati. "
msgstr "So he desires to bond with another. "

msgctxt "an7.51:3.8"
msgid "Yañcassa saṃyogapaccayā uppajjati sukhaṃ somanassaṃ tañca ākaṅkhati. "
msgstr "And he desires the pleasure and happiness that comes from such a bond. "

msgctxt "an7.51:3.9"
msgid "Purisatte, bhikkhave, abhiratā sattā itthīsu saṃyogaṃ gatā. "
msgstr "Sentient beings who are attached to their masculinity are bound to women. "

msgctxt "an7.51:3.10"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puriso purisattaṃ nātivattati. "
msgstr "This is how a man does not transcend his masculinity. "

msgctxt "an7.51:3.11"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, saṃyogo hoti. "
msgstr "This is how one is bound. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an7.51:4.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, visaṃyogo hoti? "
msgstr "And how does one become unbound? "

msgctxt "an7.51:4.2"
msgid "Itthī, bhikkhave, ajjhattaṃ itthindriyaṃ na manasi karoti—"
msgstr "A woman doesn’t focus on her own femininity: "

msgctxt "an7.51:4.3"
msgid "itthikuttaṃ itthākappaṃ itthividhaṃ itthicchandaṃ itthissaraṃ itthālaṅkāraṃ. "
msgstr "her feminine moves, feminine appearance, feminine ways, feminine desires, feminine voice, and feminine adornment. "

msgctxt "an7.51:4.4"
msgid "Sā tattha na rajjati, sā tatra nābhiramati. "
msgstr "She isn’t stimulated by this and takes no pleasure in it. "

msgctxt "an7.51:4.5"
msgid "Sā tattha arattā tatra anabhiratā bahiddhā purisindriyaṃ na manasi karoti—"
msgstr "So she doesn’t focus on the masculinity of others: "

msgctxt "an7.51:4.6"
msgid "purisakuttaṃ purisākappaṃ purisavidhaṃ purisacchandaṃ purisassaraṃ purisālaṅkāraṃ. "
msgstr "masculine moves, masculine appearance, masculine ways, masculine desires, masculine voice, and masculine adornment. "

msgctxt "an7.51:4.7"
msgid "Sā tattha na rajjati, tatra nābhiramati. "
msgstr "She isn’t stimulated by this and takes no pleasure in it. "

msgctxt "an7.51:4.8"
msgid "Sā tattha arattā tatra anabhiratā bahiddhā saṃyogaṃ nākaṅkhati. "
msgstr "So she doesn’t desire to bond with another. "

msgctxt "an7.51:4.9"
msgid "Yañcassā saṃyogapaccayā uppajjati sukhaṃ somanassaṃ tañca nākaṅkhati. "
msgstr "Nor does she desire the pleasure and happiness that comes from such a bond. "

msgctxt "an7.51:4.10"
msgid "Itthatte, bhikkhave, anabhiratā sattā purisesu visaṃyogaṃ gatā. "
msgstr "Sentient beings who are not attached to their femininity are not bound to men. "

msgctxt "an7.51:4.11"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, itthī itthattaṃ ativattati. "
msgstr "This is how a woman transcends her femininity. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.59, sc5
msgctxt "an7.51:5.1"
msgid "Puriso, bhikkhave, ajjhattaṃ purisindriyaṃ na manasi karoti—"
msgstr "A man doesn’t focus on his own masculinity: "

msgctxt "an7.51:5.2"
msgid "purisakuttaṃ purisākappaṃ purisavidhaṃ purisacchandaṃ purisassaraṃ purisālaṅkāraṃ. "
msgstr "masculine moves, masculine appearance, masculine ways, masculine desires, masculine voice, and masculine adornment. "

msgctxt "an7.51:5.3"
msgid "So tattha na rajjati, so tatra nābhiramati. "
msgstr "He isn’t stimulated by this and takes no pleasure in it. "

msgctxt "an7.51:5.4"
msgid "So tattha aratto tatra anabhirato bahiddhā itthindriyaṃ na manasi karoti—"
msgstr "So he doesn’t focus on the femininity of others: "

msgctxt "an7.51:5.5"
msgid "itthikuttaṃ itthākappaṃ itthividhaṃ itthicchandaṃ itthissaraṃ itthālaṅkāraṃ. "
msgstr "feminine moves, feminine appearance, feminine ways, feminine desires, feminine voice, and feminine adornment. "

msgctxt "an7.51:5.6"
msgid "So tattha na rajjati, tatra nābhiramati. "
msgstr "He isn’t stimulated by this and takes no pleasure in it. "

msgctxt "an7.51:5.7"
msgid "So tattha aratto tatra anabhirato bahiddhā saṃyogaṃ nākaṅkhati. "
msgstr "So he doesn’t desire to bond with another. "

msgctxt "an7.51:5.8"
msgid "Yañcassa saṃyogapaccayā uppajjati sukhaṃ somanassaṃ tañca nākaṅkhati. "
msgstr "Nor does he desire the pleasure and happiness that comes from such a bond. "

msgctxt "an7.51:5.9"
msgid "Purisatte, bhikkhave, anabhiratā sattā itthīsu visaṃyogaṃ gatā. "
msgstr "Sentient beings who are not attached to their masculinity are not bound to women. "

msgctxt "an7.51:5.10"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, puriso purisattaṃ ativattati. "
msgstr "This is how a man transcends his masculinity. "

msgctxt "an7.51:5.11"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, visaṃyogo hoti. "
msgstr "This is how one is unbound. "

msgctxt "an7.51:5.12"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho, bhikkhave, saṃyogo visaṃyogo dhammapariyāyo”ti. "
msgstr "This is the exposition of the teaching on the bound and the unbound.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an7.51:5.13"
msgid "Aṭṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

